article.headline: Arkansas 62, SE Louisiana 55
article.story: FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. -- Freshman Ky Madden scored 10 points and had seven assists off the bench to help Arkansas pull away Saturday for a 62-55 win over Southeastern Louisiana. The win snapped a two-game losing streak for the Razorbacks (6-3) and was the first of seven consecutive home games. Arkansas, which shot a combined 33 percent from the field in its last two losses on the road at Connecticut and Oklahoma, shot 47 percent in this game and scored 24 points off 20 Southeastern Louisiana turnovers. Madden's points led the Razorbacks, who also had eight points each from Mardracus Wade, Rickey Scott and Devonta Abron. Elgin Bailey led the Lions (5-4) with 12 points, and DeShawn Patterson and Daron Populist had 11 apiece. Southeastern Louisiana shot just 33 percent from the field.
